pageContext.claim: “So, number one, nothing was offered [by the World Health Organization]. Number two, it was a bad test. Otherwise, it was wonderful.”
pageContext.analysis: The World Health Organization adopted a test designed by German researchers for covid-19. The organization made the recipe public for countries to replicate the test if they have the technology to do so. The organization does provide test kits, but those are generally for countries with fewer resources than the United States. There have been no reports of problems with The WHO test.
